    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-10-04T18:28:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-10-04T18:28:00-05:00" n="89"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <head>89. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Honduras</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d89fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 715.00/10–357. Confidential; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-10-04T19:28:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 4, 1957—7:28 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Re your 134<note n="2" xml:id="d89fn2">Dated October 3. (<hi rend="italic"
                            >Ibid</hi>.)</note> Department concurs your views regarding need to
                    clarify to <persName corresp="#p_VMR1">Villeda</persName> prospects of
                    additional U.S. economic aid for Honduras and caution him against exaggerating
                    such prospects in his plans and making over-optimistic statements. <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRRJ1">Rubottom</persName> pointed out to Mejia<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d89fn3">
                        <persName>Gabriel Mejia</persName>, Minister of Economy.</note> Wednesday
                    that <gloss target="#t_IBRD1">IBRD</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_EXIMBankEximbank1">ExIm Bank</gloss> policies of financing only
                    foreign exchange costs is well known. Development Loan Fund still unknown factor
                    because criteria for use remain to be <pb facs="0228" n="194" xml:id="pg_194"/>
                    determined. We believe Honduras should exercise strict control over budgetary
                    and fiscal planning; take appropriate steps to save exchange for capital goods
                    imports; and foster private foreign investment. <persName corresp="#p_RRRJ1"
                        >Rubottom</persName> expressed opinion Honduras should start on development
                    projects which have already been studied and are ready for execution (such as
                    highway construction). He made no commitment of any kind to Mejia group.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_VMR1">Villeda</persName>’s confidence that constituent
                    assembly will name him president contrasts sharply with Armed Forces attitude as
                    expressed by Galvez in 12 page letter to Agurcia<note n="4" xml:id="d89fn4"
                        >Nicolas Aqurcia, Counsel to the Honduran Military Junta.</note> who
                    transmitted contents to Willauer by phone. Letter substantially agreed with
                    Galvez views reported Embdes 125.<note n="5" xml:id="d89fn5">Dated September 30.
                        (Department of State, Central Files, 715.00/9–3057)</note> According Galvez
                    armed forces will retain control through Junta which acting as its agent until
                    inauguration president chosen popular election and not by assembly, thus
                    fulfilling commitment to Honduran people. Current Junta submitting resignation
                    effective October 21. Armed Forces will name new Junta to operate until duly
                    elected civilian government takes charge.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
